p.m:
\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
    45\cdot\left( -{\frac{5}{9}} \right)
    \amp =\frac{45}{1} \cdot \left(-{\frac{5}{9}}\right) \amp \hbox{We can divide both the first numerator and the second denominator by 9.}\\
    \amp =\frac{5}{1} \cdot \left(-{\frac{5}{1}}\right)\\
    \amp ={-25}
    \end{aligned}}
